snippet.textDisplay:
I know everyone is always commenting on Jenny. But I love the way she looks when Peter says he should be sitting there. She realises she can’t be condescending or belittle him, like she does to other people who pitch.

I meet people like her on a weekly basis. Don’t get me wrong I would like to be wealthy and based on my current circumstances I doubt I ever will be. But people like her are out of touch and decency in life comes second to money.

I’m not an envious or jealous person and am really pleased for people who do well in life. But never put someone on a peddler stool because they have money.
snippet.textOriginal:
I know everyone is always commenting on Jenny. But I love the way she looks when Peter says he should be sitting there. She realises she can’t be condescending or belittle him, like she does to other people who pitch. 

I meet people like her on a weekly basis. Don’t get me wrong I would like to be wealthy and based on my current circumstances I doubt I ever will be. But people like her are out of touch and decency in life comes second to money. 

I’m not an envious or jealous person and am really pleased for people who do well in life. But never put someone on a peddler stool because they have money.
